HEADWORD: Tetraonid
<hw>Te*tra"o*nid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>tetrao</ets> a heath cock, grouse, Gr. <?/: cf. F.
<ets>t⟦eacute⟧traonide</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A bird
belonging to the tribe of which the genus <gen>Tetrao</gen> is the type,
as the grouse, partridge, quail, and the like. Used also
adjectively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

